---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Roadmap · Squeezy"
  description="What Squeezy is shipping next: release artifacts, benchmark publication, Windows code signing, and language coverage."
  active="docs"
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="page-hero-inner">
      <span class="eyebrow">roadmap</span>
      <h1>What's shipping next.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Squeezy is pre-1.0. The roadmap is short on purpose: a small number of
        items the next release should deliver, each with a visible status.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="roadmap">
      <article class="roadmap-item">
        <span class="status-pill ok">shipping</span>
        <div>
          <h3>First-class graph coverage across nine languages</h3>
          <p>Rust, Python, Java, C#, Go, C, C++, JavaScript, and TypeScript share the same navigation surface today: declarations, references, callers, hierarchy, flow, and exact reads.</p>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="roadmap-item">
        <span class="status-pill ok">shipping</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Six provider adapters</h3>
          <p>OpenAI, Anthropic, Google Gemini, Azure OpenAI, Amazon Bedrock, and Ollama route through one tool loop with shared cost, context, and budget accounting.</p>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="roadmap-item">
        <span class="status-pill wip">in progress</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Release-tagged install artifacts</h3>
          <p>Pin the curl installer, Homebrew tap, Winget package, and GitHub archives to tagged releases with SHA-256 sidecars and reproducible install flows.</p>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="roadmap-item">
        <span class="status-pill wip">in progress</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Reproducible cost-savings benchmark</h3>
          <p>Publish a benchmark report that pairs navigation quality with measured read bytes, tool calls, provider tokens, and a documented baseline.</p>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="roadmap-item">
        <span class="status-pill wip">in progress</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Signed Windows release</h3>
          <p>Sign the Windows x86_64 archive so SmartScreen stops flagging first runs of a fresh binary.</p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
